.TH "MediaRecorder.requestData" "JS" "February 8, 2024" "JavaScript" "JavaScript Reference Manual"
.SH NAME
MediaRecorder.requestData \- MediaRecorder: requestData() method
.SH SYNOPSIS
The \f[B]\f[CB]requestData()\f[B]\f[R] method of the
\f[CR]MediaRecorder\f[R] interface is used to raise a
\f[CR]dataavailable\f[R] event containing a \f[CR]Blob\f[R] object of
the captured media as it was when the method was called.
This can then be grabbed and manipulated as you wish.
.PP
When the \f[CR]requestData()\f[R] method is invoked, the browser queues
a task that runs the following steps:
.IP "1." 3
If \f[CR]MediaRecorder.state\f[R] is \[lq]inactive\[rq], raise a DOM
\f[CR]InvalidState\f[R] error and terminate these steps.
If \f[CR]MediaRecorder.state\f[R] is not \[lq]inactive\[rq], continue to
the next step.
.IP "2." 3
Raise a \f[CR]dataavailable\f[R] event containing a \f[CR]Blob\f[R] of
the currently captured data (the Blob is available under the event\[cq]s
\f[CR]data\f[R] attribute.)
.IP "3." 3
Create a new Blob and place subsequently captured data into it.
.SH SYNTAX
.IP
.EX
requestData()
.EE
.SS Parameters
None.
.SS Return value
None (\f[CR]undefined\f[R]).
.SS Exceptions
.TP
\f[B]InvalidStateError\f[R] \f[B]DOMException\f[R]
Thrown if the \f[CR]MediaRecorder\f[R] is currently
\f[CR]\[dq]inactive\[dq]\f[R]; you cannot capture the recording if the
\f[CR]MediaRecorder\f[R] is not active.
.SH EXAMPLES
.IP
.EX
captureMedia.onclick = () \f[B]=>\f[R] {
  mediaRecorder.requestData();
  \f[I]// makes snapshot available of data so far\f[R]
  \f[I]// ondataavailable fires, then capturing continues\f[R]
  \f[I]// in new Blob\f[R]
};
.EE
